==English==

===Etymology===
{{compound|chair|person}}, after {{term|chairman}} and {{term|chairwoman}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|pl2=chairpeople}}

# a [[chairman]] or [[chairwoman]], someone who [[preside]]s over a [[meeting]], [[board]], etc.
#: ''She was the '''chairperson''' of the board and she [[preside]]d over the meeting''.

====Usage notes====
In modern usage, terms like {{term|chair}}, {{term|moderator}}, {{term|coordinator}}, {{term|presiding}} {{term|officer}}, {{term|group}} {{term|leader}}, {{term|head}}, {{term|facilitator}}, and so forth, are often preferred.

====Synonyms====
* [[chair]]
* [[presiding]] [[officer]], [[presider]]

